## 2) Supabase official pack — **`.agents/agent-skills/skills/`**

Upstream: [`supabase/agent-skills`](https://github.com/supabase/agent-skills). Your copy lives under **`.agents/agent-skills/`** (see **`.agents/agent-skills/README.md`**).

| Situation | Read this file |
|-----------|----------------|
| Any Supabase work (Auth, DB, RLS, migrations, CLI, Edge Functions, Realtime, Storage, SSR clients, MCP) | `.agents/agent-skills/skills/supabase/SKILL.md` |
| Postgres performance, indexes, pooling, RLS review, query tuning | `.agents/agent-skills/skills/supabase-postgres-best-practices/SKILL.md` |

**Optional fallback:** if those paths are missing (e.g. fresh clone without `.agents`), use the git submodule copy: **`vendor/supabase-agent-skills/skills/...`** — run `git submodule update --init --depth 1 vendor/supabase-agent-skills`.

## Rules

- **Do not** paste the entire skill into chat unless the user asks; **read the file** and apply it.
- If **multiple** skills apply (e.g. Supabase + `tdd`), read them **in a sensible order** and state briefly which you used.
- If **none** apply, ignore this rule for that turn.
